                  </hi>.(<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 59.) On the 19th of July, about one o'clock in the morning, I met the prisoner at the top of Dock-street, with a bundle under her apron—I asked what it was—she said a gown she had been getting from the washerwoman—I asked if it contained any thing else—she said, "No," but it contained this gown, petticoat, and shift.</p>
